theorem Topology.dense_implies_P3 {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    Dense (A : Set X) → Topology.P3 (X := X) A := by
  intro hDense
  dsimp [Topology.P3]
  intro x hxA
  -- The closure of a dense set is the whole space.
  have h_closure : closure (A : Set X) = (Set.univ : Set X) := hDense.closure_eq
  -- Hence the interior of that closure is also the whole space.
  have h_int_univ : interior (closure (A : Set X)) = (Set.univ : Set X) := by
    simpa [h_closure, interior_univ]
  -- Any point of `A` therefore lies in `interior (closure A)`.
  have : (x : X) ∈ (Set.univ : Set X) := by
    simp
  simpa [h_int_univ] using this

theorem Topology.interior_closure_interior_subset_interior_closure {X : Type*}
    [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    interior (closure (interior (A : Set X))) ⊆ interior (closure A) := by
  intro x hx
  -- The inclusion `interior A ⊆ A` yields an inclusion of their closures.
  have h_closure :
      closure (interior (A : Set X)) ⊆ closure A :=
    closure_mono (interior_subset : interior (A : Set X) ⊆ A)
  -- Monotonicity of `interior` transports the point into the desired set.
  exact (interior_mono h_closure) hx

theorem Topology.P3_mono {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A B : Set X}
    (hAB : (A : Set X) ⊆ B) (hP3 : Topology.P3 (X := X) B) :
    Topology.P3 (X := X) A := by
  dsimp [Topology.P3] at hP3 ⊢
  intro x hxA
  -- Use `hP3` together with the inclusion `hAB`.
  have hxB : (x : X) ∈ interior (closure B) := hP3 (hAB hxA)
  -- Transfer from `interior (closure B)` to `interior (closure A)`.
  have h_closure_subset : closure B ⊆ closure A := closure_mono hAB
  have h_interior_subset :
      interior (closure B) ⊆ interior (closure A) :=
    interior_mono h_closure_subset
  exact h_interior_subset hxB

theorem Topology.closure_boundary_subset_closure {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    closure (closure (A : Set X) \ interior A) ⊆ closure (A : Set X) := by
  -- The boundary `closure A \ interior A` is contained in `closure A`.
  have h_subset : (closure (A : Set X) \ interior A) ⊆ closure (A : Set X) := by
    intro x hx
    exact hx.1
  -- Monotonicity of `closure` yields the desired inclusion.
  exact closure_mono h_subset

theorem Topology.boundary_subset_closureCompl {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    closure (A : Set X) \ interior A ⊆ closure (Aᶜ : Set X) := by
  intro x hx
  -- `hx` provides that `x ∈ closure A` and `x ∉ interior A`.
  have h_not_int : (x : X) ∉ interior (A : Set X) := hx.2
  -- Since `closure (Aᶜ) = (interior A)ᶜ`, the non-membership just obtained
  -- translates into membership of `x` in `closure (Aᶜ)`.
  have h_eq := Topology.closure_compl_eq_compl_interior (X := X) (A := A)
  have : (x : X) ∈ (interior (A : Set X))ᶜ := by
    simpa using h_not_int
  simpa [h_eq] using this
